@Noppey 
Sorry if I ask a silly question, but I also have an issue with my CSP and the use of the exceljs library. I adjusted my tsconfig as you've mentioned, but now I run into an error telling me regeneratorRuntime is not defined. I've tried to add the import as you've mentioned, but I'm unsure where I should add this? Ive added it in the same file where I also import Workbook from exceljs, but this doesn't seem to solve the issue. Can you point me in the good direction please? I don't like to add 'unsafe-eval' in my csp.

Thanks

That's what I'm doing as well:
import 'regenerator-runtime/runtime'; // Required for ExcelJS to work with bare.min.js version (which in turn is required to prevent unsafe-eval)
import { Workbook } from 'exceljs';

I have this on top of every component that uses the Workbook class.

Update: Maybe the order of import matters? I'm not sure.
